 TWO <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum" target="_blank">museums</a> have shut for the day after <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" target="_blank">workers</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walking" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walking" target="_blank">walked</a> out in a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Controversy" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Controversy" target="_blank">dispute</a> over <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Payment" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Payment" target="_blank">pay</a>  Around 100 <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public" target="_blank">Public</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commercial_bank" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commercial_bank" target="_blank">Commercial</a> Services <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_and_Commercial_Services_Union" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_and_Commercial_Services_Union" target="_blank">PCS</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trade_union" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trade_union" target="_blank">Union</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laborer" target="_blank">workers</a> at the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum_of_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum_of_Scotland" target="_blank">National Museum of Scotland</a> have gone <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strike_action" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strike_action" target="_blank">on strike</a> after a breakdown in talks The <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union" target="_blank">union</a> said it is attempting to get <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museum" target="_blank">museum</a> <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Management" title="h